Problem in one line

Do strings me jo continuous same part ho, uski maximum length nikaalni hai.

ðŸ’» C++ Code (Humanized comments)
int lcs(string &str1, string &str2){
    int n = str1.size();   // length of first string
    int m = str2.size();   // length of second string
    int ans = 0;           // stores the maximum length found

    // Pick every character of str1 as a starting point
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){

        // Compare it with every character of str2
        for(int j = 0; j < m; j++){

            int k = 0;  // used to move forward while characters match

            // Move forward from i and j while characters are same
            while(i + k < n && j + k < m && str1[i + k] == str2[j + k]){
                k++;   // increase length of matching substring
            }

            // Update maximum length found so far
            ans = max(ans, k);
        }
    }

    return ans;  // return the longest common substring length
}

ðŸ” Line-by-Line Dry Run

Take example:

str1 = "abcjklp"
str2 = "acjkp"


Indexes:

str1:  0 1 2 3 4 5 6
       a b c j k l p

str2:  0 1 2 3 4
       a c j k p

Step 1: i = 0 â†’ 'a'

j = 0 â†’ 'a'

k=0 â†’ a==a âœ”

k=1 â†’ b!=c âŒ
Length = 1 â†’ ans = 1

j = 1,2,3,4 â†’ no match

Step 2: i = 1 â†’ 'b'

All j pe mismatch â†’ nothing changes

Step 3: i = 2 â†’ 'c' â­ (important)

j = 1 â†’ 'c'

Now while loop:

k	str1[i+k]	str2[j+k]	Match
0	c	c	âœ”
1	j	j	âœ”
2	k	k	âœ”
3	l	p	âŒ

Length = 3

ans = 3

Substring found = "cjk"

Step 4: i = 3 â†’ 'j'

j = 2 â†’ 'j'

j==j âœ”

k==k âœ”

l!=p âŒ
Length = 2 â†’ ans still 3

Baaki sab positions pe chhote matches milte hain (1 or 2)
ðŸ§  How this code actually works

Har (i, j) ko starting point maana

while loop substring ko forward check karta hai

Mismatch aate hi substring break

Maximum length store karte jaate hain

Ye approach naturally substring ko model karta hai.
Isliye DP ki zarurat nahi padti.

â± Time Complexity

Worst case:
O(n * m * min(n, m))
But constraints (â‰¤1000) me chal jaata hai.

